<p class="">    <h2>Key Challenges in the Steering Lock Systems Market</h2>    <ul>        <li><strong>Technological Advancements:</strong> Rapid developments in automotive technology, such as the rise of autonomous vehicles and advanced driver-assistance systems (ADAS), present challenges to conventional steering lock systems. Manufacturers must continuously innovate to ensure compatibility with new technologies.</li>        <li><strong>Regulatory Compliance:</strong> Stringent regulations surrounding vehicle safety and anti-theft measures require steering lock systems to meet specific standards. Adapting to these evolving regulations can pose a significant challenge for manufacturers, increasing costs and development time.</li>        <li><strong>Theft and Security Issues:</strong> As vehicle theft persists, the effectiveness of traditional mechanical locks is increasingly questioned. Innovations are often needed to enhance security features, increasing project timelines and expenditure for companies trying to stay competitive.</li>        <li><strong>Supply Chain Disruptions:</strong> The global automotive industry has been facing supply chain disruptions, influenced by factors like the pandemic and geopolitical tensions. This can hamper the procurement of essential materials for steering lock systems, delaying production and increasing costs.</li>        <li><strong>Consumer Preferences:</strong> The growing demand for smart automotive technologies has shifted consumer preferences towards integrated security systems rather than standalone steering locks. Companies must adapt their product offerings to align with these changing preferences, which may require significant investment.</li>    </ul>    <h2>Potential Growth Opportunities in the Steering Lock Systems Market</h2>    <ul>        <li><strong>Integration with Smart Technologies:</strong> The rise of IoT devices offers opportunities for integrating steering lock systems with smart technologies, enabling rem